ğŸ§° Installation
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-project-name.git
cd your-project-name

2. Create a virtual environment (recommended)
python -m venv venv


Activate it:

Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

Linux/macOS
source venv/bin/activate

3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run the CLI
python main.py

ğŸ§ª Usage

The CLI guides you interactively.

Sending a Request

Choose an HTTP method

Enter the URL

Add headers (optional)

Add JSON body (optional for GET)

Receive a structured response:

status code

headers

body

response time

Saved Requests

Store common requests inside saved_requests.json and re-run them anytime.

Request History

Every request is automatically stored inside history.json.

ğŸ“¦ Dependencies

From requirements.txt:

requests
colorama


